te%20off%20her%20symptoms%20as%20side%20effects%20of%20pregnancy%20and%20childbirth.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EShe%20said%20a%20colonoscopy%20saved%20her%20life%20and%20could%20save%20others%2C%20as%20early%20cancers%20are%20on%20the%20rise.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20red%20flag%20for%20Marisa%20Peters%20was%20literal%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F24-year-old-diagnosed-stage-3-colon-cancer-subtle-symptom-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eblood%20on%20the%20toilet%20paper%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20birth%20of%20her%20first%20child%2C%20she%20noticed%20symptoms%20%E2%80%94%20rectal%20bleeding%2C%20changes%20to%20her%20bowel%20movements%2C%20an%20urgent%20need%20to%20go%20%E2%80%94%20which%20her%20doctors%20chalked%20up%20to%20lingering%20physical%20side%20effects%20of%20childbirth.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20took%20six%20years%20until%20she%20finally%20found%20that%20the%20underlying%20cause%20of%20her%20symptoms%20was%20stage%203%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcolon-rectal-cancer-rise-young-people-protect-yourself-lower-risk-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ecolorectal%20cancer%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20shocking%20revelation%20for%20her%20as%20she%20considered%20herself%20a%20young%2C%20healthy%20mom%20of%20three.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20really%2C%20really%20did%20not%20expect%20that%20cancer%20was%20the%20diagnosis%2C%26quot%3B%20Peters%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BI%20knew%20for%20sure%20that%20something%20was%20wrong%20the%20entire%20time.%20I%20just%20did%20not%20know%20what.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2043%20and%20cancer-free%20thanks%20to%20extensive%20treatment%2C%20Peters%20is%20channeling%20her%20experience%20to%20raise%20awareness%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrue-cost-young-colon-cancer-crisis-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Erise%20in%20young%20cancer%20cases%3C%2Fa%3E%20among%20people%20in%20their%2020s%2C%2030s%2C%20and%2040s.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20nonprofit%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbeseen.care%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBe%20Seen%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20she%20cofounded%20with%20her%20husband%20Josh%2C%20promotes%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Feasy-at-home-colon-cancer-screening-tests-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ecancer%20prevention%20resources%3C%2Fa%3E%20like%20%26quot%3Bpoop%20parties%26quot%3B%20where%20people%20gather%20to%20prep%20for%20colonoscopies%20and%20reduce%20the%20anxiety%2C%20stigma%2C%20and%20shame.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPeters%2C%20who%20lives%20in%20Los%20Angeles%2C%20said%20she%20hopes%20to%20raise%20awareness%20about%20early%20colorectal%20cancer%20symptoms%20to%20help%20others%20avoid%20the%20challenges%20she%20faced.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20had%20not%20even%20heard%20about%20the%20disease%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20more%20that%20I%20went%20through%20treatment%2C%20the%20more%20frustrated%20I%20grew%20because%20it's%20preventable.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e56eaac5-0f10-4cdd-b935-9374cbc8912f%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EDoctors%20missed%20the%20subtle%20symptoms%20of%20cancer%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EPeters%2C%20a%20Broadway%20vocalist%20turned%20advocate%2C%20describes%20herself%20as%20a%20Type%20A%20personality%20with%20big%20dreams%20and%20the%20energy%20and%20drive%20to%20match.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20she%20noticed%20changes%20to%20her%20health%20after%20the%20birth%20of%20her%20first%20son%2C%20she%20felt%20the%20doctor%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwoman-dismissed-doctors-years-diagnosed-stage-3-colon-cancer-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Edismissed%20her%20concerns%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20being%20overly%20ambitious%20about%20her%20post-pregnancy%20lifestyle.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20had%20high%20standards%20and%20expectations%20for%20myself%20and%20what%20I%20accomplish%20in%20life%2C%26quot%3B%20Peters%20said.%20%26quot%3BFrom%20a%20medical%20practitioner%20standpoint%2C%20that%20was%20interpreted%20as%20'This%20woman%20has%20unrealistic%20expectations%20of%20what%20her%20body's%20going%20to%20be%20like%20after%20having%20had%20kids.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225779%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20family%20of%20four%20in%20matching%20outfits%20on%20a%20beach%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69a76372d3e2f1aef369ef61%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223853%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EPeters%20with%20her%20husband%2C%20Josh%2C%20and%20their%20three%20children.%3Cp%3EPhoto%20by%20Larissa%20Block%2FCourtesy%20of%20Be%20Seen%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20symptoms%20persisted%20and%20intensified%20over%20time.%20She%20needed%20to%20use%20the%20bathroom%20more%20frequently%20and%20more%20urgently.%20Her%20bowel%20movements%20looked%20different%2C%20with%20smaller%2C%20ragged-edged%20stools.%20She%20saw%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frectal-bleeding-most-common-early-sign-of-colon-cancer-taboo-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eblood%20in%20her%20stool%3C%2Fa%3E%20more%20often%20and%20in%20greater%20amounts%2C%20to%20the%20point%20where%20she%20developed%20anemia.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20multiple%20doctors%20over%20many%20appointments%20said%20it%20was%20normal%20to%20feel%20different%20after%20pregnancy%20and%20childbirth.%20She%20had%20hemorrhoids%2C%20which%20can%20cause%20rectal%20bleeding%2C%20but%20that%20bleeding%20is%20also%20one%20of%20the%20most%20common%20signs%20of%20colorectal%20cancer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPeters%20thought%20she%20was%20too%20young%2C%20but%20increasingly%2C%20people%20in%20their%2020s%20and%2030s%20are%20developing%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fidentical-twins-young-colon-cancer-diagnosis-2025-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Egastrointestinal%20symptoms%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20turn%20out%20to%20be%20colorectal%20cancers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Caside%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBusiness%20Insider's%20series%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fyoung-people-cancer-crisis-risk-tips-2025-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Trust%20Cost%20of%20Young%20Cancer%2C%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20delves%20into%20the%20trend%20of%20younger%20people%20being%20diagnosed%20with%20cancer%2C%20from%20the%20unique%20financial%20challenges%20to%20the%20patchwork%20of%20fertility%20laws%20that%20young%20patients%20face.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrue-cost-young-colon-cancer-crisis-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ERead%20more.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Faside%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmong%20young%20patients%2C%20cancer%20is%20often%20diagnosed%20late%2C%20when%20survival%20rates%20are%20lower.%20For%20patients%20with%20stage%201%20colorectal%20cancer%2C%20the%20survival%20rate%20over%20five%20years%20is%20more%20than%2090%25.%20For%20patients%20with%20stage%204%2C%20the%20survival%20rate%20drops%20to%2015%25%2C%20sometimes%20less.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWaiting%20to%20act%20on%20symptoms%2C%20even%20if%20they're%20vague%2C%20can%20increase%20the%20likelihood%20of%20a%20more%20serious%20illness.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20lost%20so%20much%20time%20that%20I%20don't%20know%20if%20it's%20miraculous%2C%20lucky%2C%20or%20blessed%20that%20I%20didn't%20have%20a%20stage%20four%20diagnosis%2C%26quot%3B%20Peters%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22577318e6-48cf-4737-b1b4-0bfef0d01f99%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EColon%20cancer%20on%20the%20rise%20in%20younger%20patients%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETen%20days%20after%20Peters%20was%20diagnosed%2C%20she%20started%20a%20treatment%20plan%20that%20lasted%20nearly%20a%20year%2C%20including%20radiation%2C%20surgeries%2C%20and%20a%20dozen%20rounds%20of%20chemo.%20She%20managed%20to%20keep%20her%20energy%20up%20enough%20to%20work%20through%20the%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20treatment%20ended%20with%20the%20good%20news%20that%20she%20was%20in%20remission.%20Then%20came%20an%20unexpected%20challenge%3A%20figuring%20out%20her%20life%20and%20identity%20as%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Foncologist-diagnosed-breast-cancer-no-symptoms-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ecancer%20survivor%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BLife%20never%20goes%20back%20to%20what%20it%20was%20before%20the%20diagnosis.%20You're%20irreparably%20changed%2C%26quot%3B%20Peters%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20a%20cancer%20treatment%20ends%2C%20there's%20a%20sense%20of%20relief%20for%20friends%20and%20family%2C%20a%20feeling%20that%20the%20hard%20part%20is%20over.%20For%20patients%2C%20remission%20brings%20a%20new%20set%20of%20uncertainties.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPeters%20said%20figuring%20out%20how%20to%20understand%20her%20new%20life%20and%20the%20new%20realities%20of%20her%20body%20felt%20very%20lonely.%20She%20leaned%20into%20her%20newfound%20experience%20of%20navigating%20cancer%20diagnosis%20and%20treatment%2C%20channeling%20her%20work%20as%20an%20artist%2C%20performer%2C%20and%20leader%20to%20bring%20people%20together%20for%20the%20cause.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222210%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20woman%20in%20a%20sparkling%20sequined%20pantsuit%20holding%20a%20microphone%20in%20front%20of%20the%20Capitol.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69a764a4fd4fbd083f29782c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221658%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EPeters%20said%20advocacy%20helped%20her%20make%20sense%20of%20her%20experience%20with%20colorectal%20cancer%20treatment%20%E2%80%94%20and%20prevent%20other%20patients%20from%20getting%20a%20late%20diagnosis.%3Cp%3EPhoto%20by%20Paul%20Morigi%2C%20courtesy%20of%20Fight%20CRC%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EHer%20nonprofit%20foundation%20aims%20to%20raise%20awareness%20of%20colorectal%20cancer%20symptoms%2C%20improve%20access%20to%20preventive%20screening%2C%20such%20as%20colonoscopies%2C%20and%20empower%20people%20to%20advocate%20for%20themselves.%20The%20current%20recommended%20age%20to%20start%20colorectal%20cancer%20screening%20is%2045.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPeters%20said%20if%20she%20had%20waited%20until%20then%20for%20a%20colonoscopy%2C%20it%20may%20have%20been%20too%20late.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20really%20want%20to%20emphasize%20the%20importance%20of%20trusting%20your%20gut%20and%20your%20body%2C%26quot%3B%20Peters%20said.%20%26quot%3BYou%20know%20your%20body%20best%2C%20and%20you've%20got%20to%20be%20relentless.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdoctors-dismissed-mom-symptoms-colorectal-cancer-2026-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1773136621000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69a762c9fd4fbd083f297811%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdoctors-dismissed-mom-symptoms-colorectal-cancer-2026-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20woman%20in%20her%2030s%20was%20diagnosed%20with%20colorectal%20cancer%20after%20six%20years%20of%20doctors%20dismissing%20symptoms%2C%20believing%20they%20were%20childbirth%20side%20effects.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22glandsverk%40insider.com%20(Gabby%20Landsverk)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdoctors-dismissed-mom-symptoms-colorectal-cancer-2026-3%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Alexander%20Butterfield%2C%20who%20revealed%20Nixon%20Watergate%20tapes%2C%20dies%20aged%2099%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1773136479000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fichef.bbci.co.uk%2Fnews%2F1024%2Fbranded_news%2F8479%2Flive%2Fcacbee60-1c06-11f1-b037-333a1d6ad5d4.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2Fckg15l9welxo%230%2