2F129386716.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3ESouth%20Indian%20cinema%20is%20witnessing%20a%20surge%20in%20mega-budget%20productions%2C%20with%20'Kalki%202898%20AD'%20currently%20leading%20at%20Rs%20600%20crore.%20However%2C%20S.%20S.%20Rajamouli's%20upcoming%20'Varanasi%2C'%20starring%20Mahesh%20Babu%2C%20is%20poised%20to%20shatter%20records%20with%20an%20estimated%20Rs%201%2C200-1%2C400%20crore%20budget%2C%20promising%20a%20global%20spectacle.%20Other%20high-profile%20films%20like%20'RRR'%20and%20'Pushpa%202'%20also%20feature%20prominently.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20Entertainment%20Desk%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Americans%20are%20pulling%20money%20out%20of%20their%20401(k)%20funds%20at%20record%20rates%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224499%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Wall%20Street%20employees%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69989e01efb52c8bd0de90fe%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EMomo%20Takahashi%2C%20Business%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EAmericans%20are%20making%20early%20withdrawals%20from%20retirement%20accounts%20at%20a%20record%20pace%2C%20according%20to%20Vanguard%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EVanguard%20said%206%25%20of%20clients%20took%20hardship%20withdrawals%20in%202025%2C%20up%20from%204.8%25%20in%20the%20previous%20year.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EDespite%20more%20early%20withdrawals%2C%20average%20401(k)%20balances%20rose%2013%25%20since%202024%2C%20Vanguard%20said.%20%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EData%20from%20Vanguard%20shows%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fearly-401k-withdrawals-hardship-distributions-retirement-funds-investing-advice-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EAmericans%20are%20pulling%20money%20out%20of%20their%20retirement%20accounts%3C%2Fa%3E%20early%20at%20record%20rates%20to%20help%20make%20ends%20meet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20year%2C%206%25%20of%20Vanguard's%20clients%20took%20a%20hardship%20withdrawal%2C%20which%20allows%20them%20to%20access%20funds%20in%20tax-advantaged%20retirement%20accounts%2C%20such%20as%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Fwhat-is-401k%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3E401(k)%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20before%20they%20reach%20retirement%20age.%20That%20was%20up%20from%204.8%25%20in%202024%2C%20the%20asset%20management%20giant%20said.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETaking%20a%20hardship%20withdrawal%20is%20not%20ideal%20for%20a%20few%20reasons%2C%20one%20of%20them%20being%20that%20investors%20are%20subject%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2F401k-early-withdrawal%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ewithdrawal%20penalty%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%2010%25%20for%20taking%20money%20out%20of%20their%20account%20before%2059%C2%BD.%20On%20top%20of%20that%2C%20they%20are%20then%20taxed%20on%20any%20gains.%20However%2C%20perhaps%20most%20importantly%2C%20they%20rob%20themselves%20of%20future%20growth%20potential%20on%20that%20money%2C%20especially%20if%20they%20are%20still%20far%20from%20retirement%20age.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGiven%20these%20negatives%2C%20it's%20generally%20not%20a%20good%20sign%20that%20Americans%20are%20withdrawing%20money%20from%20their%20retirement%20accounts.%20It%20could%20signal%20that%20consumers%20are%20increasingly%20struggling%20to%20keep%20up%20with%20expenses%20and%20are%20resorting%20to%20extreme%20measures%20to%20do%20so.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Vanguard%20said%20the%20increase%2C%20taken%20in%20context%2C%20may%20not%20be%20all%20that%20concerning.%20That's%20because%20the%20number%20of%20investors%20enrolled%20in%20401(k)s%20is%20rising.%20The%20IRS%20also%20loosened%20its%20rules%20on%20receiving%20a%20hardship%20distribution%20in%202019%2C%20perhaps%20making%20them%20slightly%20more%20common.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BGiven%20that%20it's%20now%20easier%20to%20request%20a%20hardship%20withdrawal%20and%20that%20automatic%20enrollment%20is%20helping%20more%20workers%20save%20for%20retirement%2C%20especially%20lower-income%20workers%2C%20a%20modest%20increase%20isn't%20surprising%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20Vanguard%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPlus%2C%20despite%20the%20negatives%2C%20having%20an%20account%20one%20is%20able%20to%20draw%20on%20in%20times%20of%20emergency%20%E2%80%94%20even%20if%20not%20ideal%20%E2%80%94%20is%20better%20than%20having%20no%20cushion%20at%20all.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%20a%20small%20subset%20of%20workers%20facing%20financial%20stress%2C%20hardship%20withdrawals%20may%20serve%20as%20a%20safety%20net%20that%20may%20not%20otherwise%20have%20been%20available%20without%20plan-implemented%20automatic%20solutions%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EData%20from%20Fidelity%20also%20shows%20an%20increase%20in%20hardship%20withdrawals%20among%20its%20clients.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20account%20balances%20since%202024%20have%20gone%20up%20on%20the%20whole%2C%20both%20firms%20said.%20Vanguard%20reported%20an%20average%20account%20balance%20jump%20of%2013%25%20to%20%24167%2C970.%20The%20median%20balance%20was%20%2444%2C115.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20his%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftakeaways-trump-state-of-the-union-speech-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EState%20of%20the%20Union%20address%3C%2Fa%3E%20last%20week%2C%20President%20Donald%20Trump%20talked%20up%20rising%20401(k)%20balances.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20stock%20market%20is%20at%2053%20all-time%20record%20highs%20since%20the%20election.%20Think%20of%20that.%20One%20year.%20Boosting%20pensions%2C%20401(k)s%20and%20retirement%20accounts%20with%20millions%20and%20millions%20of%20Americans%2C%26quot%3B%20Trump%20said.%20%26quot%3BThey're%20all%20gaining.%20Everybody's%20up%2C%20way%20up.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F401k-hardship-withdrawals-record-retirement-savings-investment-accounts-stock-market-2025-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1773135001000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F699a68deefb52c8bd0de9f4f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F401k-hardship-withdrawals-record-retirement-savings-investment-accounts-stock-market-2025-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Vanguard%20data%20shows%20Americans%20are%20pulling%20money%20out%20of%20their%20retirement%20accounts%20early%20at%20record%20rates%20to%20help%20make%20ends%20meet.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22wedwards%40businessinsider.com%20(William%20Edwards)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F401k-hardship-withdrawals-record-retirement-savings-investment-accounts-stock-market-2025-3%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Congress%20Leader's%20%26quot%3BGiddha%20Dance%20For%20Rs%201%2C000%26quot%3B%20Post%20Sparks%20Row%20In%20Punjab%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22A%20political%20slugfest%20erupted%20between%20the%20ruling%20Aam%20Aadmi%20Party%20(AAP)%20and%20the%20Congress%20in%20Punjab%20over%20women's%20dignity%20after%20a%20social%20media%20post%20by%20Congress%20leader%20Sukhpal%20Khaira%20sparked%20controversy%20and%20drew%20sharp%20reactions%20from%20the%20treasury%20benches.%22%2C%22published%22%3A1773134973000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2026-03%2Ffeloj59s_punjab_625x300_10_March_26.jpg%3Fim%3DFitAndFill%2Calgorithm%3Ddnn%2Cwidth%3D1200%2Cheight%3D738%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fcongress-leader-sukhpal-khaira-giddha-dance-for-rs-1-000-post-sparks-row-in-punjab-aap-bhagwant-mann-government-11194483%23publisher%3Dnewsstand%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20political%20slugfest%20erupted%20between%20the%20ruling%20Aam%20Aadmi%20Party%20(AAP)%20and%20the%20Congress%20in%20Punjab%20over%20women's%20dignity%20after%20a%20social%20media%20post%20by%20Congress%20leader%20Sukhpal%20Khaira%20sparked%20controversy%20and%20drew%20sharp%20reactions%20from%20the%20treasury%20benches.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fcongress-leader-sukhpal-khaira-giddha-dance-for-rs-1-000-post-sparks-row-in-punjab-aap-bhagwant-mann-government-11194483%23publisher%3Dnewsstand%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22I%20battled%20depression%20while%20working%20in%20Big%20Tech.%20Opening%20up%20about%20my%20mental%20illness%20to%20colleagues%20made%20me%20realize%20I%20wasn't%20alone.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22852%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Two%20women%20standing%20in%20sunshine%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69af2128d3e2f1aef36a409d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22930%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ECarly%20Schwartz%2C%20left%2C%20shown%20with%20a%20former%20colleague.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Carly%20Schwartz.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ECarly%20Schwartz%20battled%20severe%20depression%20during%20her%20time%20working%20in%20Big%20Tech%20in%20the%20mid-2010s.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EShe%20had%20excellent%20health%20benefits%2C%20but%20she%20couldn't%20find%20relief%20and%20used%20drugs%20and%20alcohol%20to%20cope.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EClean%20and%20sober%20after%20rehab%2C%20she%20decided%20she%20no%20longer%20wanted%20to%20hide%20her%20struggles%20from%20colleagues.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EI%20still%20remember%20how%20mortified%20I%20felt%20the%20day%20I%20perched%20across%20from%20my%20boss%2C%20the%20head%20of%20editorial%20at%20one%20of%20the%20Bay%20Area's%20most%20ubiquitous%20Big%20Tech%20companies%2C%20on%20his%20stiff%20red%20office%20couch.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20sweaty%20palms%20and%20trembling%20knees%2C%20I%20asked%20him%20to%20grant%20me%20a%20one-month%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fquit-big-tech-after-medical-leave-feel-more-fulfilled-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Emedical%20leave%3C%2Fa%3E%20because%20my%20depression%20had%20become%20unbearable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBut%E2%80%A6what%20does%20that%20mean%3F%26quot%3B%20he%20asked.%20%26quot%3BCan%20you%20tell%20me%20more%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20struggled%20to%20find%20the%20words.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20hard%20to%20explain%2C%26quot%3B%20I%20eventually%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20just%20don't%20have%20any%20energy.%20To%20do%20anything.%20I'm%20drained%20all%20the%20time%2C%20physically.%20And%20nothing%20feels%20good%20to%20me.%20I%20hate%20myself.%20I%20only%20get%20out%20of%20bed%20to%20come%20to%20work.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20could%20tell%20my%20boss%20was%20just%20trying%20to%20approach%20an%20unfamiliar%20situation%20with%20curiosity%20and%20compassion.%20He%20granted%20my%20leave%20without%20hesitation%20and%20found%20someone%20else%20on%20our%20team%20to%20cover%20for%20me.%20Nevertheless%2C%20I%20exited%20his%20office%20humiliated.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2267be93eb-9b57-4114-8a5f-e1ecf8a9722a%5C%22%3EMy%20mental%20illness%20had%20reached%20a%20crescendo%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EA%20few%20months%20earlier%2C%20in%20the%20fall%20of%202016%2C%20I'd%20returned%20home%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoved-san-francisco-worth-it-cost-of-living-negativity-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ESan%20Francisco%3C%2Fa%3E%20after%20a%20disastrous%20stint%20in%20Panama%2C%20where%20I'd%20spent%20the%20past%20year%20trying%20to%20open%20a%20journalism%20school%20in%20a%20jungle%20eco-community.%20I%20was%2031%20years%20old%20and%20had%20worked%20as%20an%20editor%20in%20a%20high-octane%20newsroom%20for%20most%20of%20my%20adult%20life%2C%20and%20I%20thought%20I%20could%20outrun%20my%20blossoming%20depression%20by%20%26quot%3Bchasing%20my%20bliss%26quot%3B%20to%20the%20equator.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%2C%20my%20mental%20illness%20reached%20a%20crescendo%2C%20and%20I%20wound%20up%20on%20a%20one-way%20flight%20back%20to%20the%20States%20at%20the%20advice%20of%20a%20kind%20stranger%20on%20the%20other%20end%20of%20a%20suicide%20hotline.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnemployed%2C%20unraveling%2C%20and%20uninsured%2C%20I%20enrolled%20in%20a%20state-sponsored%20health%20plan%20to%20begin%20treating%20my%20condition%20in%20earnest.%20But%20in-network%20mental%20health%20care%20for%20my%20crappy%20insurance%20amounted%20to%20long%20waits%20and%20limited%20providers.%20I%20needed%20a%20job%20that%20afforded%20me%20better%20coverage.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20a%20rare%20spurt%20of%20motivation%2C%20I%20stumbled%20upon%20a%20listing%20for%20an%20internal%20news%20editor%20on%20the%20communications%20team%20at%20one%20of%20Silicon%20Valley's%20most%20dominant%20tech%20empires%2C%20a%20company%20whose%20name%20had%20become%20a%20verb.%20Its%20top-tier%20employee%20benefits%20%E2%80%94%20including%20the%20holy%20grail%20of%20health%20insurance%20%E2%80%94%20had%20been%20common%20knowledge%20since%20its%20inception.%20In%20an%20extraordinary%20collision%20of%20luck%20and%20timing%2C%20I%20managed%20to%20land%20the%20role.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftech-companies-employees-prove-productivity-rto-performance-reviews-ai-investments-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EBig%20Tech%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20mid-2010s%20was%20a%20fever%20dream%20of%20professional%20opulence.%20I%20immediately%20found%20a%20therapist%20and%20started%20on%20yet%20another%20medication%20regimen.%20Yet%20my%20depression%20persisted.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20trudged%20through%20the%20dazzling%20campus%20in%20a%20daze%2C%20passing%20volleyball%20courts%20and%20sipping%20iced%20tea%20from%20the%20custom%20boba%20bar%2C%20wanting%20to%20die.%20I%20zoned%20out%20during%20team%20lunches%2C%20hands%20shaking%20from%20my%20meds%2C%20trying%20not%20to%20spill%20soup%20down%20my%20shirt%20as%20my%20colleagues%20recounted%20their%20vibrant%20weekends.%20Since%20I'm%20a%20good%20enough%20faker%20to%20blend%20in%2C%20nobody%20ever%20noticed%20I%20wasn't%20okay.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20dissonance%20was%20not%20lost%20on%20me%3A%20In%20one%20of%20the%20most%20resource-rich%20environments%20on%20the%20planet%2C%20I%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fquitting-big-tech-decade-industry-two-layoffs-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ecouldn't%20find%20a%20way%20to%20alleviate%20my%20pain%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Having%20access%20to%20everything%20and%20finding%20relief%20in%20nothing%20sent%20me%20further%20into%20a%20vortex%20of%20guilt%20and%20shame.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20work%2C%20I%20channeled%20every%20shred%20of%20my%20meager%20cognitive%20energy%20into%20completing%20my%20tasks%20satisfactorily%2C%20and%20to%20anyone%20else%2C%20it%20seemed%20like%20I%20was%20doing%20just%20fine%20in%20my%20new%20role.%20The%20rest%20of%20the%20time%2C%20I%20hid%20under%20the%20covers%20or%20drank%20to%20the%20point%20of%20blacking%20out%20%E2%80%94%20the%20two%20fastest%20shortcuts%20to%20escaping%20my%20own%20mind.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2253539f21-0c2f-4be1-b347-0fd804879e02%5C%22%3EI%20took%20a%20medical%20leave%2C%20and%20then%20another%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20first%20medical%20leave%2C%20granted%20during%20that%20awkward%20exchange%20on%20my%20boss's%20red%20couch%2C%20took%20place%20in%20an%20outpatient%20program%20at%20a%20local%20psychiatric%20hospital.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20course%20of%20several%20group%20therapy%20sessions%2C%20I%20learned%20that%20two%20of%20the%20other%20people%20in%20the%20program%20had%20the%20same%20employer%20as%20me.%20They%20were%20battling%20their%20own%20mental%20health%20issues%2C%20their%20gold-plated%20insurance%20cards%20yielding%20similar%20benefits%20as%20mine.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20we%20navigated%20our%20respective%20darkness%2C%20we%20still%20managed%20to%20recognize%20our%20relative%20privilege.%20How%20did%20suffering%20people%20who%20didn't%20have%20fancy%20health%20insurance%20access%20the%20care%20they%2C%20too%2C%20so%20desperately%20needed%3F%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20outpatient%20program%20didn't%20end%20up%20helping%20me%20much.%20Neither%20did%20transcranial%20magnetic%20stimulation%20therapy%2C%20which%20my%20health%20insurance%20covered%2C%20or%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fbusinessinsider.com%2Fketamine-therapy-depression-treatment-addictive-drug-clinics-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eketamine%20infusions%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20I%20paid%20for%20out%20of%20pocket%20but%20received%20on%20company%20time.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20a%20year%20and%20a%20half%20of%20trudging%20through%20life%20at%20bare%20minimum%2C%20I%20decided%20to%20try%20residential%20rehab.%20I%20found%20a%20facility%20that%20took%20Big%20Tech%20health%20insurance%20and%20off%20I%20went.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAgainst%20all%20odds%2C%20rehab%20ended%20up%20being%20the%20antidote%20I%20needed.%20Two%20years%20flattened%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbusiness-leaders-who-openly-discuss-drug-and-alcohol-addiction%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Esevere%20depression%20meant%20drugs%20and%20alcohol%3C%2Fa%3E%20had%20become%20my%20favorite%20coping%20mechanism%20outside%20of%20languishing%20in%20bed.%20The%20residential%20rehab%20program%20took%20me%20down%20avenues%20toward%20the%20root%20of%20my%20illness%20that%20I'd%20never%20before%20traversed.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20with%20a%20clean%20and%20sober%20mind%2C%20for%20the%20first%20time%20in%20my%20adult%20life%2C%20I%20had%20a%20fighting%20chance%20of%20treating%20my%20condition%20in%20earnest.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22a0f1cbf7-7142-4386-83ed-928d38c2002f%5C%22%3ENow%2C%20I'm%20open%20about%20my%20struggles%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20returned%20to%20work%2C%20I%20decided%20I%20no%20longer%20wanted%20to%20keep%20my%20mental%20illness%20a%20secret.%20I%20felt%20better%20than%20I%20had%20in%20years%2C%20maybe%20ever.%20Tentatively%20embracing%20the%20newfound%20confidence%20that%20comes%20with%20self-love%20and%20sobriety%2C%20I%20started%20talking%20to%20my%20colleagues%20about%20what%20I'd%20been%20through.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20started%20small%3A%20a%20walk%20between%20meetings%2C%20a%20candid%20conversation%20over%20afternoon%20coffee.%20The%20more%20I%20shared%2C%20the%20more%20I%20realized%20just%20how%20common%20my%20story%20was.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20coworkers%20began%20disclosing%20every%20flavor%20of%20the%20same%20topic%20to%20me%2C%20confiding%20their%20own%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fformer-facebook-microsoft-exec-says-amazon-warehouse-job-cured-burnout-2022-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Epersistent%20depression%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20problematic%20drinking%2C%20or%20asking%20for%20advice%20about%20supporting%20a%20loved%20one%20with%20similar%20challenges.%20I%20helped%20a%20few%20folks%20navigate%20our%20generous-but-labyrinthine%20benefits%20program%20so%20they%20could%20access%20the%20same%20resources%20that%20helped%20me.%20I%20even%20worked%20with%20our%20People%20Operations%20department%20to%20ensure%20offsite%20events%20would%20be%20inclusive%20of%20non-drinkers.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20was%20seven%20years%20ago%2C%20and%20I've%20remained%20sober%20and%20depression-free%20ever%20since.%20I%20even%20served%20as%20a%20spokesperson%20for%20the%20tech%20company's%20%26quot%3Brecovery%20month%26quot%3B%20campaign.%20When%20I%20left%20my%20full-time%20job%20in%202021%20for%20new%20adventures%20as%20a%20journalist%2C%20writer%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-fired-burnout-depression-grigory-yakushev-2021-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Emental%20health%3C%2Fa%3E%20advocate%2C%20discourse%20around%20these%20issues%20among%20my%20colleagues%20had%20begun%20to%20bubble%20to%20the%20surface%20more.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20know%20every%20company%20is%20different.%20I%20know%20I%20got%20unfathomably%20lucky.%20I%20also%20know%2C%20now%2C%20that%20while%20I%20might%20have%20concealed%20my%20condition%20at%20first%2C%20I%20wasn't%20alone%20in%20my%20suffering.%20The%20more%20these%20conversations%20come%20to%20the%20forefront%2C%20the%20better%20off%20we%20all%20are.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEvery%20once%20in%20a%20while%2C%20I%20still%20worry%20that%20disclosing%20my%20struggles%20so%20candidly%20might%20have%20negative%20repercussions.%20But%20I'm%20determined%20to%20never%20return%20to%20that%20dark%2C%20lonely%20place%2C%20and%20it%20wasn't%20until%20I%20stopped%20hiding%20that%20I%20started%20to%20see%20the%20light.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ECarly%20Schwartz%20is%20a%20San%20Francisco-based%20author%20whose%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%2F%3Fh%3D239f714d22dd519fa1a8339d76d51fa6babc3994079536000e0c8fa417a1cbb8%26postID%3D69af1d6a2ecd2440019010f3%26postSlug%3Dhid-my-depression-big-tech-job-how-i-got-help-2026-3%26tags%3Dservice%253Acapi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fbookshop.org%252Fp%252Fbooks%252Fi-ll-try-anything-twice-misadventures-of-a-self-medicated-life-carly-schwartz%252F591dca26d9b8c510%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Enew%20memoir%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%2C%20I'll%20Try%20Anything%20Twice%2C%20chronicles%20her%20recovery%20adventures.%20She%20served%20as%20editor-in-chief%20of%20the%20SF%20Examiner%20and%20founding%20editor%20of%20HuffPost's%20SF%20bureau%2C%20runs%20a%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mindwriters.co%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Eworkshop%20series%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20focused%20on%20storytelling%20for%20healing%2C%20and%20yammers%20about%20the%20writing%20process%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcarlyink.substack.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%