ter%20getting%20fired.%3Cp%3EANGELA%20WEISS%20%2F%20AFP%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbobbi-brown-layers-are-dumb-doesnt-believe-in-consultants-2025-11%5C%22%20data-autoaffiliated%3D%5C%22false%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EFounder%20Bobbi%20Brown%3C%2Fa%3E%20said%20she%20felt%20like%20a%20%26quot%3Bloser%26quot%3B%20after%20Est%C3%A9e%20Lauder%20cut%20her%20creative%20contract%20in%202016.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EBrown%20said%20she%20worked%20on%20herself%20and%20stayed%20busy%20while%20she%20determined%20her%20next%20move.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EAfter%20her%20non-compete%20expired%20in%202020%2C%20Brown%20launched%20Jones%20Road%20Beauty.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EBobbi%20Brown%20said%20she%20felt%20defeated%20when%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbobbi-brown-shares-exit-namesake-brand-aftermath-2025-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EEst%C3%A9e%20Lauder%20cut%20her%20creative%20contract%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20her%20namesake%20brand%20in%202016.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20brand%20didn't%20technically%20fire%20her%2C%20but%20she%20equates%20the%20two.%20The%20beauty%20conglomerate%20cut%20her%20work%20contract%20while%20offering%20to%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eallow%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eher%20to%20remain%20the%20face%20of%20the%20company.%20Brown%2C%20as%20a%20result%2C%20said%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eshe%20felt%20like%20she%20had%20no%20choice%20but%20to%20leave.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20felt%20like%20such%20a%20loser%2C%26quot%3B%20Brown%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20While%20few%20people%20experience%20this%20exact%20sort%20of%20exit%2C%20there%20are%20lessons%20anyone%20can%20learn%20from%20Brown's%20story.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcool-girls-guide-bouncing-back-after-layoff-firing-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ELosing%20your%20job%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20and%20figuring%20out%20what%20to%20do%20next%20%E2%80%94%20is%20never%20easy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHer%20first%20piece%20of%20advice%20for%20those%20who%20find%20themselves%20in%20a%20similar%20situation%20is%20to%20%26quot%3Brealize%20it's%20normal%20to%20feel%20these%20things%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20it's%20a%20necessary%20part%20of%20the%20process.%20But%20Brown%20said%20she%20doesn't%20encourage%20staying%20in%20a%20slump.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20up%20to%20you%20if%20you%20want%20to%20spend%20six%20months%20in%20bed%20being%20sad%20%E2%80%94%20or%20you%20want%20to%20try%20to%20feel%20better%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20doesn't%20mean%20forcing%20yourself%20to%20feel%20better%20overnight.%20Brown%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Esaid%20that%20in%20the%20months%20that%20followed%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eit%20was%20hard%20to%20hear%20that%20the%20company%20was%20going%20on%20without%20her.%20But%20she%20kept%20herself%20busy%20and%20tried%20to%20a%20better%20place%20mentally%20and%20figure%20out%20what%20she%20wanted%20to%20do%20next.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BStanding%20still%20is%20not%20an%20option%2C%26quot%3B%20Brown%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBrown%20said%20she%20had%20a%20%26quot%3Bspiritual%20chiropractor%26quot%3B%20who%20helped%20her%20release%20bad%20energy%2C%20and%20also%20saw%20a%20business%20coach%20during%20that%20time.%20Eventually%2C%20she%20started%20to%20get%20back%20to%20the%20mindset%20of%20%26quot%3Bwhat%20could%20be.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEst%C3%A9e%20Lauder%20didn't%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20not%20someone%20that%20likes%20to%20stay%20sad%20or%20mad%2C%20so%20I%20just%20worked%20on%20myself%20%E2%80%94%20from%20the%20inside%20out%2C%26quot%3B%20Brown%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20her%20memoir%20%26quot%3BStill%20Bobbi%2C%26quot%3B%20Brown%20wrote%20about%20how%20she%20developed%20resilience%20during%20her%20teenage%20years%2C%20as%20she%20was%20faced%20with%20her%20mom%20and%20brother's%20mental%20illnesses%20and%20her%20parent's%20divorce.%20Brown%20wrote%20that%20she%20still%20feels%20pain%20from%20those%20events%20at%20times%2C%20but%20she%20doesn't%20let%20it%20consume%20her%20or%20hold%20her%20back.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2208894be6-8e1b-4ce1-b13f-1a8c0b075332%5C%22%3EFinding%20her%20second%20act%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBrown%20said%20she%20never%20imagined%20she'd%20still%20be%20working%20in%20her%2060s%20%E2%80%94%20in%20fact%2C%20that%20was%20part%20of%20why%20she%20agreed%20to%20a%2025-year%20non-compete%20with%20Est%C3%A9e%20Lauder%20upon%20exiting%20the%20brand.%20But%20in%20the%20years%20that%20followed%2C%20she%20said%20she%20felt%20rejuvenated%20by%20her%20work%20and%20spending%20time%20with%20so%20many%20young%20people%20that%20she%20felt%20like%20she%20was%20in%20her%2030s%20again.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20those%20endeavors%20was%20promoting%20her%20book%2C%20%26quot%3BBeauty%20From%20the%20Inside%20Out%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20she%20announced%20shortly%20after%20leaving%20Est%C3%A9e%20Lauder.%20She%20described%20it%20as%20the%20ideal%20book%20to%20mark%20her%20%26quot%3Brebirth.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20had%20things%20to%20look%20forward%20to%20and%20occupy%20my%20mind%20and%20do%20differently%2C%26quot%3B%20Brown%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20she%20figured%20out%20her%20next%20career%20steps%2C%20she%20experimented%20with%20various%20ventures%2C%20including%20a%20short-lived%20supplement%20brand%20and%20a%20shop%20at%20Lord%20%26amp%3B%20Taylor%20called%20%26quot%3BJustBobbi%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20included%20a%20curated%20selection%20of%20her%20favorite%20products.%20She%20said%20the%20shop%20combined%20her%20love%20of%20content%20creation%20with%20coming%20up%20with%20new%20products%2C%20and%20gave%20her%20the%20support%20of%20a%20big%20company%20and%20the%20freedom%20to%20assemble%20a%20team.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEventually%2C%20Brown's%20various%20projects%20led%20her%20to%20her%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbobbi-brown-makeup-aging-influencers-interview-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Esecond%20act%3A%20Jones%20Road%20Beauty.%3C%2Fa%3E%20Today%2C%20the%20clean%20beauty%20brand%20is%20known%20for%20its%20viral%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.jonesroadbeauty.com%2Fproducts%2Fmiracle-balm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EMiracle%20Balm%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20blush%20and%20bestselling%20foundation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20that%20when%20she%20launched%20it%20October%202020%20%E2%80%94%20when%20her%20noncompete%20expired%20%E2%80%94%20she%20thought%20it%20would%20be%20a%20%26quot%3Bsmall%2C%20little%2C%20fun%20creative%20brand%26quot%3B%20and%20hoped%20to%20reach%20%241%20million%20in%20revenue%20the%20first%20year.%20The%20brand%20ended%20up%20exceeding%20that%2C%20and%20hit%20roughly%20%24160%20million%20by%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20recent%20interview%20with%20Bloomberg's%20David%20Rubenstein%2C%20Brown%20described%20her%20departure%20from%20her%20former%20employer%20as%20%26quot%3Bthe%20best%20thing'%26quot%3B%20to%20happen%20to%20her.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20doing%20something%20that%20I%20should%20be%20doing%2C%20and%20that%20I%20love%2C%26quot%3B%20Brown%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20if%20I%20didn't%20go%20through%20the%20bad%20stuff%2C%20I%20wouldn't%20be%20able%20to%20come%20out%20on%20this%20end.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjones-road-bobbi-brown-advice-second-act-2026-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1773134401000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69ab38db1fb3fcb426491761%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjones-road-bobbi-brown-advice-second-act-2026-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Brown%20told%20Business%20Insider%20she%20felt%20bad%20after%20leaving%20her%20namesake%20brand.