%20is%20still%20in%20the%20six-figure%20range.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20lowest%20among%20the%20engineering%20degrees%20was%20industrial%20at%20%24100%2C000.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20chart%20below%20shows%20the%2010%20majors%20with%20the%20highest%20median%20mid-career%20pay%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FD8AYh%2F1%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22College%20major%20outcomes%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22515%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOne%20of%20the%20strongest%20predictors%20of%20high%20mid-career%20wages%20is%20high%20early-career%20wages%2C%26quot%3B%20Zhao%20said.%20%26quot%3BGetting%20a%20leg%20up%20early%20on%20helps%20set%20workers%20onto%20a%20higher%20earning%20trajectory%20for%20the%20rest%20of%20their%20career.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20analysis%20showed%20engineering%20majors%20ranked%20highly%20for%20early-career%20wages%2C%20too.%20Computer%20engineering%20had%20the%20highest%20early-career%20median%20wage%2C%20at%20%2490%2C000%2C%20followed%20by%20computer%20science%20at%20%2487%2C000.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22bcc7a39b-541c-4e81-b453-aac9fc574b83%5C%22%3EBeing%20a%20millennial%20versus%20a%20newcomer%20in%20the%20job%20market%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20New%20York%20Fed's%20analysis%20of%2035-%20to%2045-year-olds%20includes%20a%20large%20share%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillennial-economy-finances-jobs-homeownership-boomer-parents-2025-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Emillennial%20generation%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20data%20is%20from%202024%2C%20so%20it%20doesn't%20reflect%20the%20most%20recent%20job%20market%20in%202025%2C%20when%20the%20US%20added%20the%20fewest%20jobs%20over%20the%20year%20since%202003%20outside%20recessions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMillennials%20have%20been%20around%20weak%20job%20markets%20before%2C%20having%20%26quot%3Bhad%20the%20fortune%20to%20graduate%20into%20the%202008%20housing%20crisis%2C%20live%20through%20the%20Covid%20recession%20and%20be%20in%20the%20management%20ranks%20during%20the%20current%20post-Covid%20slowdown%2C%26quot%3B%20Zhao%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20job%20market%20now%20is%20soft%2C%20but%20many%20of%20the%20lessons%20are%20the%20same%20as%20previous%20downturns.%26quot%3B%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20isn't%20in%20a%20recession%2C%20but%20the%20job%20market%20has%20been%20unusually%20frozen%20amid%20still%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Feconomy-job-market-divide-k-shape-economy-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Estrong%20gross%20domestic%20product%20growth%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Both%20overall%20unemployment%20and%20layoffs%20remain%20fairly%20low%2C%20but%20some%20big%20names%20are%20making%20job%20cuts%2C%20and%20employers%20are%20coming%20off%20a%20year%20filled%20with%20a%20lot%20of%20uncertainty.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBureau%20of%20Labor%20Statistics%20data%20showed%20unemployment%20for%2035-%20to%2044-year-olds%2C%20regardless%20of%20education%2C%20has%20remained%20low%2C%20at%203.3%25%20in%20February.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20job%20market%20tends%20to%20be%20tougher%20for%20those%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhighest-paying-jobs-high-school-associate-no-bachelors-masters-degree-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ewithout%20a%20college%20degree%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20those%20new%20to%20the%20workforce.%20Many%20older%20millennials%20were%20just%20graduating%20or%20early%20in%20their%20careers%20during%20the%20Great%20Recession%20and%20its%20long%2C%20slow%20recovery.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EZhao%20is%20optimistic%20that%20the%20job%20market%20will%20still%20need%20engineers%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ealthough%20it%20may%20be%20tougher%20for%20new%20engineering%20majors%20to%20find%20a%20job%20quickly%2C%20depending%20on%20the%20kind%20of%20engineering%20they%20studied.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEngineering%20skills%20are%20going%20to%20remain%20in%20high%20demand%20for%20years%20to%20come%2C%20but%20this%20will%20vary%20over%20time%2C%20with%20the%20business%20cycle%2C%20and%20between%20engineering%20fields%2C%26quot%3B%20Zhao%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EZhao%20said%20new%20computer%20science%20and%20engineering%20graduates%20are%20having%20a%20rough%20time%20landing%20jobs%20because%20hiring%20in%20the%20tech%20sector%20has%20been%20sluggish.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECollege%20grad%20Andrew%20Chen%20experienced%20this%20firsthand.%20Last%20May%2C%20Chen%20was%20close%20to%20earning%20his%20computer%20science%20degree%20from%20the%20University%20of%20California%20San%20Diego.%20But%20the%20excitement%20of%20graduation%20was%20clouded%20by%20the%20fact%20that%20he%20still%20hadn't%20secured%20a%20job.%20Then%20Amazon%20reached%20out%20to%20schedule%20an%20interview%2C%20and%20by%20the%20time%20he%20graduated%2C%20he'd%20accepted%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-job-how-to-get-interview-software-engineering-tiktok-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Esoftware%20engineering%20role%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20a%20six-figure%20salary.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20was%20the%20first%20big%20company%20that%20had%20given%20me%20a%20chance%20in%20a%20while%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Bso%20I%20really%20wanted%20to%20get%20this%20one.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhigh-paying-college-majors-mid-career-stage-2026-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1773133921000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69a88973d3e2f1aef369fd21%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhigh-paying-college-majors-mid-career-stage-2026-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Several%20engineering%20studies%20ranked%20among%20the