ts%20are%20designed%20to%20be%20tax-advantaged%2C%20long-term%20savings%20vehicles%20for%20families%20to%20leverage%20on%20behalf%20of%20children%20born%20in%20the%20US%20between%202025%20and%202028.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESeemingly%20even%20better%20than%20the%20tax%20benefits%20is%20the%20fact%20that%20the%20accounts%20include%20a%20%241%2C000%20government%20deposit%20when%20they're%20opened.%20Families%20can%20also%20make%20annual%20contributions%20of%20up%20to%20%245%2C000%2C%20which%20can%20be%20invested%20until%20the%20child%20turns%2018.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20benefit%20caught%20my%20eye%20%E2%80%94%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhired-house-manager-1200-month-worth-it-2025-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EI'm%20a%20financial%20planner%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20many%20clients%20who%20are%20parents%2C%20am%20a%20parent%20myself%2C%20and%20am%20always%20interested%20in%20better%20understanding%20potential%20financial%20benefits%20for%20my%204-year-old%20daughter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20jumped%20at%20the%20opportunity%20to%20analyze%20the%20benefits%20and%20drawbacks%20of%20these%20accounts%2C%20both%20for%20myself%20and%20for%20my%20clients.%20Here's%20what%20I%20found%2C%20and%20what%20I've%20shared%20with%20clients.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d4168d60-f61f-4ee1-8bf6-106233c7cce6%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20biggest%20benefit%3A%20an%20extra%20%241%2C000%20to%20your%20name%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ELet's%20start%20with%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftrumpaccounts.gov%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%241%2C000%20deposit%20made%20by%20the%20Federal%20government%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20children%20born%20between%20January%201%2C%202025%2C%20and%20December%2031%2C%202028%2C%20who%20are%20US%20citizens%20with%20a%20Social%20Security%20number.%20This%20is%20the%20primary%20highlight%20of%20Trump%20Accounts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20have%20an%20eligible%20child%2C%20signing%20up%20to%20receive%20the%20deposit%20is%20worth%20considering.%20While%20an%20extra%20%241%2C000%20on%20your%20balance%20sheet%20is%20great%2C%20that%20alone%20may%20not%20be%20enough%20to%20make%20Trump%20Accounts%20a%20superior%20savings%20option%20for%20your%20own%20cash%20versus%20alternative%20vehicles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20specific%20reasons%20that%20the%20combination%20of%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstarted-529-college-plan-son-money-tight-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E529%20plan%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20a%20taxable%20investment%20account%20serves%20as%20a%20better%20option%20for%20your%20own%20contributions%20to%20your%20children's%20financial%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22ca68137a-70f1-4a58-b447-fed756e2e9d9%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20529%20plan%20allows%20for%20more%20college%20savings%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EA%20Trump%20Account%20acts%20similarly%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Fwhat-is-a-traditional-ira%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Etraditional%20IRA%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20except%20that%20a%20child%20doesn't%20need%20earned%20income%20to%20contribute.%20Withdrawals%20after%20age%2018%20are%20subject%20to%20ordinary%20income%20tax%2C%20with%20a%2010%25%20penalty%20if%20withdrawn%20before%20age%2059%C2%BD%2C%20unless%20used%20for%20qualified%20education%20expenses%20or%20a%20first-time%20home%20purchase%20(both%20limited%20in%20nature).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20your%20primary%20goal%20is%20to%20save%20for%20college%2C%20I%20usually%20recommend%20using%20a%20529%20plan%20for%20ongoing%20cash%20contributions%20over%20a%20Trump%20Account%20because%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20529%20plan%20has%20higher%20contribution%20limits%20(based%20on%20the%20state's%20aggregate%20limit)%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E529s%20offer%20more%20diversified%20investment%20options%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThere%20are%20potential%20state%20tax%20deductions%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20SECURE%20Act%202.0%2C%20passed%20in%202022%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbeyondyourhammock.com%2Fsecure-act%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emade%20it%20possible%20to%20convert%20some%20529s%20into%20Roth%20IRAs%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%226891e311-8de3-4f18-a772-5b8f471ae5c0%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20taxable%20investment%20account%20gives%20more%20flexibility%20to%20budding%20investors%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EPerhaps%20your%20goal%20is%20to%20help%20jump-start%20your%20child's%20investment%20experience.%20In%20that%20case%2C%20a%20taxable%20investment%20account%20would%20offer%20much%20more%20flexibility%20over%20a%20Trump%20Account%2C%20thanks%20to%20the%20ability%20to%20deploy%20globally%20diversified%20portfolios%20with%20no%20contribution%20limits.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrump%20Accounts%20are%20limited%20to%20investing%20within%20mutual%20funds%20or%20ETFs%20that%20track%20a%20US%20stock%20index%20(e.g.%2C%20S%26amp%3BP%20500).%20This%20means%20global%20investments%20are%20not%20an%20option%2C%20which%2C%20for%20us%20as%20professional%20investment%20managers%2C%20represents%20a%20critical%20lack%20of%20diversity%20that%20can%20hurt%20long-term%20returns.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22cbc962a2-5930-4ca9-a1a9-ce6dd09fff47%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20Trump%20Account%20is%20fine%20to%20have%20in%20the%20mix%2C%20but%20user%20experience%20presents%20a%20big%20question%20mark%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ENone%20of%20this%20is%20to%20say%20that%20you%20should%20avoid%3Cem%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3Ea%20Trump%20Account%20if%20you%20have%20an%20eligible%20child%20who%20can%20receive%20the%20%241%2C000%20government%20contribution.%20It's%20money%20on%20the%20table%2C%20so%20you%20may%20want%20to%20take%20advantage%20if%20you%20qualify.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere%20are%20more%20details%20on%20eligibility%20and%20how%20contributions%20will%20work%20when%20the%20accounts%20go%20live%20in%20May%2C%20with%20initial%20%241%2C000%20deposits%20starting%20in%20July%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EContributions%20are%20made%20with%20after-tax%20dollars%20and%20are%20not%20tax-deductible.%20Employers%20may%20also%20contribute%20up%20to%20%242%2C500%20per%20child%20annually.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EOnce%20a%20child%20turns%2018%2C%20the%20account%20acts%20like%20a%20traditional%20IRA.%20Kids%20can%20withdraw%20from%20the%20accounts%2C%20but%20the%20withdrawal%20will%20be%20subject%20to%20a%2010%25%20early%20withdrawal%20penalty%2C%20just%20like%20other%20tax-advantaged%20accounts%2C%20if%20the%20money%20is%20taken%20out%20and%20used%20for%20non-qualified%20purposes.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EWithdrawals%20before%20age%2018%20are%20not%20allowed.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ECustomer%20support%20availability%20and%20user%20interface%20experience%20are%20also%20big%20question%20marks%20right%20now.%20Because%20these%20are%20a%20completely%20new%20type%20of%20account%20and%20will%20be%20administered%20by%20the%20Treasury%20at%20first%20(versus%20a%20large%20custodial%20institution%20like%20Fidelity%20or%20Schwab)%2C%20there%20may%20be%20bugs%20to%20work%20out%20for%20early%20adopters.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22124cc363-f69f-4c1c-bcf8-52ec3cdcd4cd%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EPersonally%2C%20I'm%20happy%20with%20our%20current%20savings%20strategy%20for%20our%20daughter%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20have%20a%20529%20plan%20for%20her%2C%20which%20we%20contribute%20to%20regularly.%20We%20also%20have%20a%20taxable%20investment%20account%20earmarked%20for%20her.%20If%20she%20had%20been%20born%20in%20the%20eligible%20period%20between%202025%20and%202028%2C%20we%20probably%20would%20not%20open%20a%20Trump%20Account%20for%20a%20few%20specific%20reasons%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EI%20don't%20like%20the%20unknown%20and%20uncertainty%20around%20having%20the%20Treasury%20administer%20these%20accounts%20versus%20an%20established%20custodian%2C%20specifically%20in%20the%20business%20of%20platforming%20investment%20accounts%20like%20Fidelity%2C%20Schwab%2C%20or%20Vanguard.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20investment%20options%20within%20the%20accounts%20are%20more%20limited%20and%20less%20diversified%20than%20the%20portfolios%20I%20prefer%20to%20construct%20for%20long-term%20growth.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EI%20would%20not%20like%20the%20uncertainty%20around%20what%20future%20administrations%20may%20or%20may%20not%20do%20with%20Trump%20Accounts.%20In%20such%20a%20politically%20polarized%20environment%2C%20I%20don't%20think%20it's%20unreasonable%20to%20expect%20a%20future%20administration%20to%20take%20steps%20to%20rescind%20or%20change%20the%20rules%20around%20Trump%20Accounts%20to%20make%20them%20less%20favorable%20savings%20vehicles.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EWe're%20not%20dissuading%20our%20eligible%20clients%20from%20opting%20in%20to%20a%20Trump%20Account.%20It's%20a%20simple%20way%20to%20get%20a%20savings%20jump-start%2C%20even%20if%20the%20only%20money%20in%20the%20account%20is%20the%20initial%20%241%2C000%20contribution.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20we're%20also%20looking%20at%20their%20broader%20financial%20plan%20and%20reminding%20them%20they%20have%20a%20choice%20about%20whether%20to%20use%20this%20account.%20For%20most%2C%20it%20will%20not%20serve%20as%20a%20critical%20piece%20of%20their%20overall%20financial%20strategy%20either%20way.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-accounts-vs-529-plans-which-better-college-savings-2026-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1773133501000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69af1f1cfd4fbd083f29c8bd%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-accounts-vs-529-plans-which-better-college-savings-2026-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Eric%20Roberge%2C%20a%20financial%20advisor%2C%20weighs%20the%20benefits%20of%20Trump%20Accounts%20against%20flexible%20alternatives%20like%20529%20plans%20and%20taxable%20investment%20accounts.%22%2C