While%20industry%20chatter%20suggested%20a%20potential%20change%20due%20to%20city-based%20titles%2C%20Khan%20dismissed%20these%20rumors%2C%20emphasizing%20the%20film's%20current%20title.%20A%20separate%20title%20rights%20issue%20is%20reportedly%20being%20resolved.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20Entertainment%20Desk%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fnews%2Faamir-khan-denies-changing-the-title-of-sunny-deol-preity-zinta-starrer-lahore-1947-where-did-you-hear-that%2Farticleshow%2F129382997.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22How%20rage%20room%20happy%20hours%20became%20all%20the%20rage%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%228943%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20group%20of%20colleagues%20from%20a%20school%20in%20the%20Bronx%20smashes%20teacups%2C%20printers%20and%20other%20electronics%20in%20a%20%26quot%3Brage%20room%26quot%3B%20on%20Thursday%2C%20February%2019%2C%202026.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69af29f3ccda166eed3d0930%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225962%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3ECorrie%20Aune%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20her%2035th%20birthday%2C%20Deja%20Monet%20decided%20she%20wanted%20to%20break%20something.%20So%20on%20a%20Tuesday%20afternoon%20in%20March%2C%20she%20and%20her%20boyfriend%20headed%20to%20The%20Ragery%2C%20a%20%26quot%3Brage%20room%26quot%3B%20on%20Manhattan's%20Lower%20East%20Side%2C%20grabbed%20a%20helmet%20and%20a%20pair%20of%20googles%2C%20and%20picked%20up%20a%20sledgehammer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20was%20so%20stressful%20about%20Monet's%20life%20that%20she'd%20spend%20the%20next%20half%20hour%20taking%20aim%20at%20stacks%20of%20plates%2C%20an%20old%20computer%20monitor%2C%20and%20a%20keyboard%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWork%2C%26quot%3B%20Monet%20said%2C%20without%20missing%20a%20beat.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMonet%2C%20a%20special-ed%20high%20school%20teacher%2C%20clarified%20that%20the%20kids%20aren't%20the%20problem.%20It's%20the%20rest%20of%20it%3A%20the%20endless%20paperwork%2C%20shifting%20lesson%20plans%2C%20and%20constant%20assessments.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInside%20the%20rage%20room%2C%20Monet%20was%20tentative%20at%20first%2C%20but%20then%20entered%20a%20flow%20state%2C%20conjuring%20up%20something%20that%20was%20bothering%20her%20before%20taking%20each%20swing.%20Then%3A%20Boom!%20She'd%20never%20done%20anything%20like%20this%20before%2C%20and%20it%20was%20thrilling.%20A%20half%20hour%20later%2C%20%26quot%3Bit%20looked%20like%20an%20explosion%20had%20happened%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20session%2C%20Monet%20said%2C%20did%20the%20trick%2C%20at%20least%20temporarily.%20%26quot%3BIt%20was%20just%20this%20huge%20sense%20of%20calmness%2C%26quot%3B%20Monet%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERage%20rooms%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Faxe-throwing-bars-popular-millennials-photos-2020-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eax-throwing%3C%2Fa%3E%20studios%20aren't%20a%20new%20concept.%20But%20in%20an%20era%20when%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fforget-ai-heres-the-real-reason-the-job-market-sucks-2025-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAmerican%20workers%20are%20stressed%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finside-rise-layoff-support-groups-lucrative-influencers-careers-employment-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efacing%20layoffs%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fquiet-cracking-warning-signs-work-employees-for-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estuck%20in%20jobs%20they%20don't%20like%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20worried%20their%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftech-jobs-getting-demolished-great-recession-dot-com-era-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecareers%20could%20turn%20obsolete%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20they're%20having%20a%20moment.%20They're%20finding%20a%20niche%20as%20venues%20for%20corporate%20team-building%20events%20and%20becoming%20after-work%20hangout%20spots%20where%20coworkers%20can%20bond%20and%20let%20off%20a%20little%20steam.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20The%20Ragery%2C%20corporate%20bookings%20have%20more%20than%20doubled%20from%20a%20year%20ago%2C%20as%20of%20January%2C%20said%20Bogdan%20Zhukovskyi%2C%20its%20co-owner.%20For%20individuals%2C%20packages%20range%20from%20%2478.38%2C%20which%20covers%2015%20minutes%20in%20a%20room%20outfitted%20with%20four%20ceramic%20items%20and%20one%20%26quot%3Bsmall%20office%20tech%2C%26quot%3B%20to%20%24522.50%20for%20a%2045-minute%20%26quot%3BVIP%20Experience%2C%26quot%3B%20where%20the%20room%20can%20be%20set%20up%20like%20a%20full%20office%2C%20and%20customers%20are%20free%20to%20take%20a%20swing%20at%20anything%20in%20sight.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECustomers%20are%20encouraged%20to%20personalize%20their%20setup.%20Zhukovskyi%20has%20seen%20coworkers%20come%20in%20with%20pictures%20of%20their%20bosses%2C%20which%20they%20affix%20onto%20the%20objects%20and%20antique%20detritus%20piled%20up%20in%20the%20rooms.%20He%20recalled%20one%20customer%20showing%20up%20with%20a%20stack%20of%20email%20printouts%2C%20which%20he%20then%20got%20to%20work%20reducing%20to%20confetti.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20Ragery%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69af2c68441e48aec3a1c40c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ERage%20rooms%20and%20ax-throwing%20studios%20are%20having%20a%20moment.%20The%20Ragery%2C%20on%20Manhattan's%20Lower%20East%20Side%2C%20offers%20packages%20ranging%20from%20%2478.38%20to%20%24522.50.%3Cp%3ECorrie%20Aune%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EExperts%20I%20talked%20to%20added%20a%20note%20of%20caution%20for%20anyone%20seeking%20this%20kind%20of%20therapy%3A%20smashing%20something%20may%20feel%20good%20in%20the%20moment%20%E2%80%94%20but%20it%20doesn't%20necessarily%20make%20you%20less%20angry.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20a%20strange%20moment%20in%20the%20American%20workplace%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-employee-engagement-workplace-morale-careers-boomers-gen-x-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Emorale%20is%20slipping%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftech-jobs-getting-demolished-great-recession-dot-com-era-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ejobs%20are%20disappearing%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20yet%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fquiet-quitting-already-over-layoffs-jobs-recession-economy-2022-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ehardly%20anyone%20is%20quitting%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWorker%20sentiment%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.adpresearch.com%2Femployee-sentiment-2026february%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edown%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20February%20for%20the%20sixth%20straight%20month%2C%20with%20drops%20in%20motivation%20and%20commitment%20across%20industries%20and%20job%20types%2C%20according%20to%20a%20report%20from%20the%20ADP%20Research%20Employee%20Motivation%20and%20Commitment%20Index.%20Meanwhile%2C%20federal%20data%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffred.stlouisfed.org%2Fseries%2FJTSQUR%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eshows%3C%2Fa%3E%20quit%20rates%20are%20hovering%20near%20their%20lowest%20levels%20in%20a%20decade.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECompounding%20workplace%20stress%2C%20many%20top%20companies%20have%20embraced%20a%20more%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftech-industry-amazon-microsoft-meta-google-companies-intensity-hardcore-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3Bhardcore%26quot%3B%20management%20culture%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20raising%20performance%20expectations%2C%20increasing%20accountability%2C%20and%20mandating%20sweeping%20return-to-office%20policies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20traditional%20after-work%20happy%20hour%20has%20meanwhile%20disappeared%20from%20a%20lot%20of%20workplaces%2C%20in%20part%20because%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-sober-non-alcoholic-economy-restaurants-events-boom-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Epeople%20are%20drinking%20much%20less%3C%2Fa%3E.%20(The%20US%20drinking%20rate%20just%20hit%20a%2090-year%20low%2C%20according%20to%20Gallup.)%20The%20American%20Psychological%20Association%20reports%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-most-accomplished-loneliest-generation-blame-parents-fault-2022-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eloneliness%20and%20emotional%20disconnection%3C%2Fa%3E%20%26quot%3Bhave%20become%20a%20defining%20feature%20of%20life%20in%20America.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYounger%20workers%2C%20especially%2C%20are%20embracing%20a%20more%20intentional%20and%20fulfilling%20way%20to%20connect%20with%20colleagues%2C%20often%20through%20physical%20activities%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcoworker-bonding-events-other-than-drinking-happy-hour-fitness-classes-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecold%20plunges%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frun-club-making-friends-dating-app-alternatives-2024-7%23%3A~%3Atext%3DIn%2520an%2520increasingly%2520online%2520world%2CZ%252C%2520says%2520CMO%2520Melissa%2520Hobley%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erunning%20clubs%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20and%20rage%20rooms%2C%20which%20offer%20a%20novel%20experience%20where%20you%20can%20bond%2C%20get%20your%20blood%20flowing%2C%20and%2C%20perhaps%2C%20release%20some%20pent-up%20feelings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20Rage%20Cage%20in%20Brooklyn%2C%20where%20packages%20range%20from%2C%20%2469.99%20to%20%24224.99%2C%20patrons%20don%20white%20jumpsuits%20to%20smash%20their%20way%20through%20plates%20and%20an%20assortment%20of%20small%20and%20large%20vintage%20electronics.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20always%20hear%20'I%20didn't%20think%20I%20needed%20that%2C%20but%20I%20feel%20so%20much%20better%20now%2C'%26quot%3B%20said%20Jeffrey%20Yip%2C%20its%20owner.%20%26quot%3BEven%20if%20you%20think%20you're%20not%20stressed%20out%2C%20and%20you%20come%20and%20break%20things%2C%20you'll%20feel%20better.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYip%20recalled%20one%20man%20who%20showed%20up%20wearing%20a%20three-piece%20suit%20and%20announced%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20got%20laid%20off.%20I%20need%20this.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%229204%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22At%20the%20Ragery%20on%20Manhattan's%20Lower%20East%20Side%2C%20a%20group%20of%20colleagues%20from%20a%20school%20in%20the%20Bronx%20prepares%20to%20enter%20a%20%26quot%3Brage%20room%26quot%3B%20on%20Thursday%2C%20February%2019%2C%202026%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69af2b2582b35e2c04dd60ca%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%226136%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAmerican%20workers%20are%20embracing%20alternatives%20to%20traditional%20%26quot%3Bhappy%20hour%26quot%3B%20meetups.%20These%20often%20involve%20physical%20activities%20like%20cold%20plunges%2C%20running%20clubs%2C%20and%20visits%20to%20rage%20rooms.%3Cp%3ECorrie%20Aune%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20not%20just%20employees%20who%20are%20embracing%20these%20venues%3B%20companies%20also%20see%20the%20appeal%20of%20giving%20employees%20an%20outlet%20for%20their%20desire%20to%20smash%20things.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20ax-throwing%20chain%20Bury%20the%20Hatchet%2C%20which%20has%20locations%20across%20the%20country%20and%20where%20a%20one-hour%20session%20costs%20around%20%2448%20per%20person%2C%20corporate%20events%20now%20make%20up%20the%20majority%20of%20business.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20some%20cases%2C%20companies%20will%20rent%20out%20the%20facility%20for%20three%20hours%2C%20throw%20for%20two%2C%20and%20then%20dedicate%20an%20hour%20to%20a%20meeting%2C%20said%20Jay%20Veloso%2C%20the%20chain's%20chief%20marketing%20officer.%20%26quot%3BThey're%20like%2C%20'Let's%20take%20it%20out%20of%20the%20whole%20professional%20sit-down%20atmosphere%20and%20let's%20do%20something%20fun%2C%20but%20also%20still%20have%20a%20professional%20part%20about%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20Veloso%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20those%20with%20something%20specific%20to%20work%20out%2C%20the%20venue%20allows%20throwers%20to%20pin%20images%20representing%20all%20kinds%20of%20irritants%20%E2%80%94%20an%20overbearing%20manager%2C%20say%2C%20or%20a%20company's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Feveryone-hates-workday-human-resources-customer-service-software-fortune-500-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Emuch-despised%20software%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20to%20different%20rings%20on%20the%20target.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAx-throwing%20is%20cheaper%20than%20therapy%2C%26quot%3B%20Veloso%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPerhaps.%20But%20are%20the%20benefits%20even%20a%20little%20bit%20comparable%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20well-established%20that%20exercise%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdaily-habits-neuroscientist-brain-training-super-ager-longevity-2025-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Esocializing%20can%20help%20relieve%20stress%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcardiologist-simple-habits-protect-heart-health-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eimprove%20resilience%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20boost%20your%20mood.%20Swinging%20a%20sledgehammer%20or%20an%20ax%20can%20also%20be%20a%20fun%20new%20thing%20to%20try%20%E2%80%94%20a%20welcome%20break%20from%20being%20too%20sedentary%20and%20too%20much%20time%20spent%20on%20our%20phones.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20digitalization%20of%20our%20lives%20leaves%20us%20craving%20something%20more%20hands-on%20%E2%80%94%20almost%20barbaric%20%E2%80%94%20to%20quench%20that%20inner%20thirst%2C%26quot%3B%20Zhukovskyi%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20was%20the%20case%20for%20Ally%20Temsey%2C%2025%2C%20who%20works%20in%20social%20media%20marketing%20in%20New%20York%20and%20recently%20hung%20out%20with%20three%20coworkers%20for%20the%20first%20time%20outside%20of%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%229377%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20Ragery%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69af2bd3441e48aec3a1c3f2%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%226251%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ERage%20room%20devotees%20say%20the%20experience%20feels%20cathartic.%20Experts%20caution%20there's%20a%20risk%20of%20%26quot%3Bexacerbating%20angry%20feelings.%26quot%3B%3Cp%3ECorrie%20Aune%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20ended%20up%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frage-room-helped-process-repressed-anger-emotions-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Evisiting%20a%20rage%20room%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20they%20saw%20as%20a%20welcome%20excuse%20to%20escape%20social%20media%20and%20their%20phones.%20It%20also%20gave%20them%20an%20opportunity%20to%20hang%20out%20and%20show%20some%20vulnerability.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20already%20had%20a%20great%20relationship%2C%20but%20this%20built%20it%20even%20stronger%20because%20we%20understand%20each%20other's%20pressure%2C%26quot%3B%20Temsey%20said.%20%26quot%3BYou're%20being%20human%2C%20and%20you're%20remembering%20that%20we%20are%20people%20outside%20of%20our%20jobs.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20while%20rage%20rooms%20are%20fine%20as%20a%20novel%20experience%20or%20for%20team%20bonding%2C%20experts%20stress%20that%20they%20are%20not%20a%20sustainable%20or%20especially%20effective%20way%20to%20manage%20anger.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20keeps%20the%20angry%20thoughts%20at%20the%20surface%2C%20where%20you're%20thinking%20about%20them%2C%20because%20you're%20acting%20on%20them%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Ryan%20Martin%2C%20a%20psychologist%20and%20author%20of%20multiple%20books%20on%20anger%20management%20who's%20known%20as%20%26quot%3Bthe%20Anger%20Professor.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you're%20relying%20on%20that%20as%20your%20anger%20management%20strategy%2C%26quot%3B%20Martin%20said%2C%20it%20could%20end%20up%20%26quot%3Bexacerbating%20angry%20feelings%20and%20making%20you%20more%20aggressive.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20concern%20was%20echoed%20by%20Brad%20Bushman%2C%20a%20professor%20at%20Ohio%20State%20University%20who%20has%20testified%20before%20Congress%20about%20youth%20violence.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20ticked%20off%20yoga%2C%20breathwork%2C%20and%20mindfulness%20as%20more%20effective%20strategies%20for%20managing%20anger%20without%20suppressing%20unpleasant%20feelings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EMonet%20didn't%20appreciate%20the%20intensity%20of%20her%20experience%20at%20The%20Ragery%20until%20a%20few%20hours%20after%20her%20visit%2C%20when%20she%20noticed%20how%20sore%20her%20muscles%20were.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe's%20not%20sure%20she'll%20become%20a%20regular%20%E2%80%94%20so%20much%20of%20the%20thrill%20was%20in%20the%20novelty.%20But%20she%20can%20see%20herself%20going%20back%20at%20least%20a%20second%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20can%20see%20it%20as%20an%20alternative%20for%20people%20who%20want%20to%20seek%20out%20other%20outlets%20to%20express%20their%20emotions%20in%20a%20positive%20way%2C%26quot%3B%20Monet%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20it%20was%20also%20a%20nice%20thing%20to%20share%20with%20her%2033-year-old%20boyfriend%2C%20Joaquin%20Terrero.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETerrero%2C%20a%20lawyer%2C%20had%20tagged%20along%20to%20help%20celebrate%20Monet's%20birthday.%20He%20ended%20up%20thoroughly%20enjoying%20the%20experience.%20He%20%26quot%3Bcouldn't%20stop%20smiling%20after%26quot%3B%20and%20left%20feeling%20%26quot%3Blighter%20in%20spirit%20and%20energized%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOf%20course%2C%20work%20isn't%20the%20only%20source%20of%20strain%20that%20might%20leave%20one%20wanting%20to%20throw%20something.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%227650%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20group%20of%20colleagues%20from%20a%20school%20in%20the%20Bronx%20smashes%20a%20phone%2C%20a%20microwave%20and%20other%20electronics%20in%20a%20%26quot%3Brage%20room%26quot%3B%20on%20Thursday%2C%20February%2019%2C%202026.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69af2b64441e48aec3a1c3e3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225100%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EWork%20stress%20and%20heartbreak%20are%20among%20the%20top%20reasons%20people%20visit%20rage%20rooms%2C%20the%20studios%20say.%20As%20one%20person%20put%20it%3A%20%26quot%3BNo%20one%20throws%20harder%20than%20a%20person%20who's%20just%20been%20broken%20up%20with.%26quot%3B%3Cp%3ECorrie%20Aune%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EEveryday%20problems%20%E2%80%94%20especially%20heartbreak%20%E2%80%94%20have%20long%20fueled%20the%20smashing%20business%20and%20continue%20to%20be%20a%20driving%20factor%20for%20people%20who%20break%20objects%20in%20their%20free%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENearly%20every%20rage%20room%20owner%20I%20spoke%20to%20said%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpublic-breakups-business-people-end-relationships-restaurants-bars-gen-z-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Egetting%20dumped%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20the%20top%20reason%20people%20give%20when%20they%20walk%20through%20the%20door.%20February%2C%20in%20particular%2C%20was%20a%20busy%20month%20for%20heartbreak%20victims.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20a%20lot%20of%20catharsis%20in%20chucking%20a%20piece%20of%20metal%20at%20a%20chunk%20of%20wood%2C%20and%20it's%20not%20doing%20us%20any%20use%20keeping%20anger%20inside%2C%26quot%3B%20Jackson%20Pierce%2C%20a%20supervisor%20at%20Kick%20Axe%20Throwing%20in%20Brooklyn%2C%20said%20of%20the%20studio's%20appeal.%20%26quot%3BHere%2C%20you%20allo